               <p>SIXTH DAY. WEDNESDAY, SEPTEMBER 20.</p>
               <p>Fourth Middlesex Jury - before Mr. Common Sergeant.</p>
               <p>1617. 
               <persName id="t18260914-305-defend1647" type="defendantName">
                  MICHAEL 
                  COLLINS
               <interp inst="t18260914-305-defend1647" type="surname" value="COLLINS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260914-305-defend1647" type="given" value="MICHAEL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260914-305-defend1647" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260914-305-defend1647" type="age" value="24"></interp>
                  </persName>
             and 
               <persName id="t18260914-305-defend1648" type="defendantName">
                  HUGH 
                  HASTINGS
               <interp inst="t18260914-305-defend1648" type="surname" value="HASTINGS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260914-305-defend1648" type="given" value="HUGH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260914-305-defend1648" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             were indicted for <rs id="t18260914-305-off1723" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18260914-305-off1723" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260914-305-off1723" type="offenceSubcategory" value="pocketpicking"></interp>
               stealing, on the <rs id="t18260914-305-cd1724" type="crimeDate">26th of August</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18260914-305-off1723 t18260914-305-cd1724"></join>, 1 sovereign, and 1 sixpence, the monies of 
                     <persName id="t18260914-305-victim1649" type="victimName">
                        Edward 
                        Rhind
                     <interp inst="t18260914-305-victim1649" type="surname" value="Rhind"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18260914-305-victim1649" type="given" value="Edward"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18260914-305-victim1649" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18260914-305-off1723 t18260914-305-victim1649"></join>
                     </persName>
                  , from his person
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>EDWARD RHIND. On the evening of the 26th of August, I received one sovereign, three shillings, and a half-crown; I tied it in the corner of a towel and put it into my hat; I went to the Grapes public-house with an old shopmate, and he treated me - I then went towards home in Willow-street, Vauxhall; I was crossing near the <placeName id="t18260914-305-crimeloc1725">Sanctuary</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18260914-305-crimeloc1725" type="placeName" value="Sanctuary"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18260914-305-crimeloc1725" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18260914-305-off1723 t18260914-305-crimeloc1725"></join> to avoid a coach; the two prisoners were walking near the Sanctuary - I ran against Collins; I turned round and begged his pardon; he muttered something - I said, "Don't be offended, I will stand a glass of gin to make all right;" I took off my hat to get a sixpence; Collins knocked it all out of my hand - I stooped and picked up three shillings and sixpence - Hastings took up a sovereign and a sixpence, and went away - I said to Collins, "Through your knocking that down, I have lost a sovereign and a sixpence" - he said, "D - n your eyes go after the man;" I took him to the watch-<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182609140130"></xptr>house, and they said, I must take him to Queen-square; when I got out, he ran away; I ran and caught him by the sword-belt; I took him to the office, but the Magisstrate discharged him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18260914-305-person1650">
                  DANIEL 
                  SULLIVAN
               <interp inst="t18260914-305-person1650" type="surname" value="SULLIVAN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260914-305-person1650" type="given" value="DANIEL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260914-305-person1650" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was with Rhind on the 26th of August between five and six o'clock - I saw a sovereign and some silver in his possession; he took off his hat, and drew a towel out; he placed the money in the corner of it, and put it on his head.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18260914-305-person1651">
                  WILLIAM 
                  HALL
               <interp inst="t18260914-305-person1651" type="surname" value="HALL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260914-305-person1651" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260914-305-person1651" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a constable. On the 28th of August I was sent by the Magistrate to the Mews, to apprehend Hastings; I found fourpence on him.</p>
               <p>HASTING'S Defence. The prosecutor himself searched me before I got from him; he found two shillings and threepence, which I said was mine, and he gave it me again.</p>
               <p>RHIND. He ran away directly, I had not time to do it.</p>
               <p>HASTINGS - <rs id="t18260914-305-verdict1726" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18260914-305-verdict1726" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 24.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18260914-305-punish1727" type="punishmentDescription">
